==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nasoturbinal
<hw>Na`so*tur"bi*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Naso-</ets> + <ets>turbinal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Connected with, or near, both the turbinal and the nasal bones;
<as>as, the <ex>nasoturbinal</ex> bone, made up of the uppermost
lammelae of the ethmoturbinal, and sometimes united with the
nasal</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The nasoturbinal
bone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nassa</ent>⟦br⟧
